# Project Conventions Override

Use this rule as the highest-priority project convention when external skills conflict with local docs.

## Canonical local skill

- Treat `.cursor/skills/boilerplate-project-standards/SKILL.md` as the canonical implementation skill for this repository.
- Apply it for all coding tasks in this repo before relying on external generic skills.

## Source of truth

- Prefer local docs under `docs/` and existing code patterns over generic remote skill defaults.
- If a skill conflicts with local docs, follow local docs and this rule.

## Auth metadata policy (this repo)

- `user_metadata.user_type` is accepted for app-level role checks in query/action helpers.
- Keep existing `authQuery` and middleware patterns unless explicitly asked to migrate them.
- Do not rewrite authorization logic to `app_metadata` unless requested.

## UI and form conventions (this repo)

- Use the local `Button` API with `isLoading`, `icon`, and `iconLeft` props.
- For forms, use `src/components/ui/form/*` wrappers and existing `FormField`/`FormItem` patterns.
- Follow `docs/ui/button.md` and `docs/ui/form.md` over external shadcn skill form conventions.

## Data layer conventions (this repo)

- Use `@tanstack/react-query` v5 APIs and current project patterns.
- Place query hooks in `src/hooks/queries/*` and mutation hooks in `src/hooks/mutations/*`.
- Follow `docs/data/react-query.md` and `docs/data/mutations-and-actions.md` for error handling.
